Only one command:
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="org-src-container"&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class="lang-lisp"&gt;sudo apt-get install emacs24-el
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
How I locate that package emacs24-el:
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class="org-src-container"&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class="lang-sh"&gt;sudo apt-get install apt-file;sudo apt-file update;
apt-file search help.el.gz
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
BTW, I assign hot key &lt;code&gt;C-h C-f&lt;/code&gt; to command &lt;code&gt;find-function&lt;/code&gt; which "Find the definition of the FUNCTION near point".&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>emacs</category><category>en</category><category>ubuntu</category><guid>http://blog.binchen.org/posts/how-to-install-emacs-source-code-under-ubuntu.html</guid><pubDate>Mon, 12 Aug 2013 11:44:00 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>